I wish to make a donation to research

     *

I wish to make a donation to research
       Donations made to the Centre Léon Bérard represent a boost to
       cancer research. You can opt to make a one-off donation or set up a
       standing order with the amount and frequency of your choice.
       Faire un don
     *

Organize a collection
       Every year, hundreds of people organize collections on the occasion
       of personal events (tribute to a loved one, wedding, birthday,
       sporting challenge such as taking part in a marathon or the Tour de
       France cycle race,…).
       Organize a collection
     *

Take part in an event
       The Centre Léon Bérard organizes or participates in sports events
       for the benefit of research carried out on its site. Such events
       bring together thousands of people in pursuit of a shared goal: to
       push back the disease through advances in research.
       Participate
     *

Bequests, donations and life insurance
       Bequeathing all or part of your estate enables you to pass on to
       future generations the best possible hope of triumphing over
       cancer. Donations and life insurance policies are also an effective
       way to take action by associating your name with the fight against
       cancer.
       Learn more
     *

Tax on Real Estate Wealth (IFI)
       Making a donation to the Centre Léon Bérard within the context of
       the Tax on Real Estate Wealth allows you to arrange your taxation
       for the benefit of a medical and scientific strategy focused on
       excellence and innovation for the benefit of the patient. This is a
       powerful gesture of generosity.
       IFI
     *

Philanthropy
       Becoming a philanthropist means linking your company with the fight
       against cancer and supporting innovation in your region. This is a
       generous move that enables you to give more substantial resources
       to the research projects developed at the Centre Léon Bérard in
       Lyon.
       Philanthropy

Why should you support us?

     *

Cancer: the leading cause of death in France
     *

Innovation in oncology and expertise in Lyon
     *

Tax deductibility
     *

Rigor and transparency

     *

Cancer: the leading cause of death in France
       Cancer is the leading cause of death in France. Every year, more
       than 400 000 new cases are diagnosed and nearly 150 000 people die
       of cancer. It is estimated that one French citizen in three will be
       affected by the disease in the course of his or her life. Thanks to
       advances in research, we now cure more than half of cancer
       patients, against one in three 30 years ago. In this fight,
       research is our best hope of finding effective and durable
       solutions for vanquishing this disease.
     *

Innovation in oncology and expertise in Lyon
       Supporting the Centre Léon Bérard means supporting the work of
       close to 500 researchers who dedicate their efforts every day to
       the fight against cancer. Bringing together patients, doctors and
       researchers on the same site addresses a key ambition of our
       institute: shortening the time needed between discoveries in the
       laboratory and their real-life application for the benefit of
       patients. Recognized internationally, the research carried out on
       the Centre Léon Bérard site is at the cutting edge of excellence
       and innovation.
     *

Tax deductibility
       As the Centre Léon Bérard is recognized as being of public benefit,
       donations made to it are eligible for a tax deduction. If you are
       subject to income tax, you can deduct 66% of the amount of your
       donations up to a maximum of 20% of your taxable income. For
       example, a donation of €50 would cost €17 after tax deduction. If
       you are subject to corporate income tax, 60% of the amount of your
       donation can be deducted up to 0.5% of turnover.
     *

Rigor and transparency
       In supporting the Centre Léon Bérard, you can be assured that your
       donations and bequests will be properly used. Our accounts are
       certified each year by an auditor and our activity reports can be
       consulted at any time on our website or are available on request.
       The CLB also undertakes to keep you regularly informed about the
       use of your donations and the various projects carried out with
       your help.

What are your donations used for?

     *

15% of the research budget
     *

Construction and equipment of research buildings
     *

Acquisition of high-tech equipment
     *

Funding research posts
     *

Patient comfort

     *

15% of the research budget
       Each year, donations made to the Centre Léon Bérard represent
       around 15% of the budget allocated to research on the whole of our
       site. This is essential financial support that enables our teams to
       go further and faster in the battle against cancer and to be at the
       cutting edge of innovation. Against the background of continual
       cuts in public funding for research, this generosity from the
       general public is fundamental to our ability to continue our fight,
       to find new treatments and continuously to improve the care we give
       to the patients at our hospital.
     *

Construction and equipment of research buildings
       Your donations provide financing to construct and equip our
       research buildings. Thanks to our donors’ generosity, we have
       recently been able to open two of the three unfinished floors of
       our newest research building, Cheney B. Opened in 2014, this
       seven-floor building had not been completed due to a lack of
       funding. With the help of an unprecedented fund-raising campaign, 3
       million euros were collected and used for fitting out the building.
       In 2016 and 2017, two floors were opened one after the other, ready
       to provide facilities to new research teams. Work is in progress to
       finish fitting out the last floor.
     *

Acquisition of high-tech equipment
       Thanks to your support, the Centre Léon Bérard is able to obtain
       state-of-the-art high-tech research equipment. Recently, DNA
       sequencers costing several hundreds of thousands of euros arrived
       to complete the facilities of the research laboratories. They
       enable researchers to read the DNA of the tumors of adult and child
       patients, in order to detect any anomalies that can explain why
       their cancer developed. With the help of this technology, doctors
       can then personalize treatments in line with the genetic profile of
       each patient’s tumor.
     *

Funding research posts
       With your donations, the Centre Léon Bérard funds around 25 posts
       each year for researchers who join the teams on its site. These are
       often post-docs who, once they have obtained their PhDs, have to
       gain experience before becoming eligible for tenure. By giving
       these young researchers financial support, usually for a period of
       three years, the Centre Léon Bérard brings additional human
       resources to teams that need reinforcement, ensures that there is a
       new generation of researchers, and gives research the resources to
       go further and faster in the fight against cancer.
     *

Patient comfort
       Every year, part of the sum obtained from donations is dedicated to
       the comfort of patients – adults and children – who are being
       treated on the Centre Léon Bérard site. This support enables our
       institute to offer patients, without charge, the services of a
       socio-esthetician and a chiropodist, to organize cultural workshops
       as part of the ‘Art in the Hospital’ program (music, photography,
       fashion, etc.), or to give Christmas presents to children and young
       people in hospital. In 2018, donations also made it possible to
       create, within the hospital, the ‘Pyramid Space’ (Espace Pyramide)
       – a 300 m² space that is unique in France, used for appropriate
       physical exercise for the adolescents, young adults and adults with
       cancer.

So that we can go further

     *

Showing solidarity
       You would like to show your support to our cause ? Hundreds of
       volunteers have mobilized to support the researchers and care staff
       of our hospital by organizing concerts, running races : contact us
       if you would like to do something for our hospital !
       Contact us
     *

Partner associations
       Every year, the Centre Léon Bérard can count on the support of some
       50 associations that organize a variety of events for the benefit
       of cancer research. Many other associations also work to assist and
       support patients in the hospital.
     * Associations working for the children of our hospital
